 filename‚ÜêGetCiderGlobalConfigFilename;folder;txt
‚çù Returns the name of the Cider config file.
‚çù As a side effect it creates the file with defaults if it does not yet exist.
 folder‚ÜêGetCiderGlobalConfigHomeFolder
 :If ~‚éïNEXISTS filename‚Üêfolder,'config.json'
     ‚çù Create a global Cider config file with default entries (all comments)
     txt‚Üê''
     txt,‚Üê‚äÇ,'{'
     txt,‚Üê‚äÇ,'  // AskForDirChange: 1,'
     txt,‚Üê‚äÇ,'  // CheckForDropboxConflicts: 0,'
     txt,‚Üê‚äÇ,'  // HandleLinkStops: 0,'
     txt,‚Üê‚äÇ,'  // ExecuteAfterProjectOpen: "",'   ‚çù ‚éïSE.Path2Function for example
     txt,‚Üê‚äÇ,'  // ReportGitStatus: 1,'
     txt,‚Üê‚äÇ,'  // verbose: 0,'
     txt,‚Üê‚äÇ,'}'
     (‚äÇtxt)‚éïNPUT filename
 :EndIf
